NMB BANK has pledged to work closely with the government to ensure that Geita residents receive quality education and health services. The remarks were made by NMB Lake zone Region Manager Mr Baraka Ladislaus during a brief handover ceremony of beds, mattresses and bed sheets at Katoro Health Center as well as the provision of 200 desks, 50 tables and 50 chairs for primary and secondary schools in Geita. "The total support we have provided is 10 beds, 10 mattresses, 30 sheets for Katoro health center, 50 tables and 50 chairs for Magenge secondary school, 50 desks for Msufini primary school and Bahari primary school 50 desks, 50 desks for Mtakuja Primary school with 50 desks for mchongomani primary school and all the equipment are worth 30 million Tanzanian shillings," he said. He added, "NMB Bank thanks Geita District Council authority for being at the forefront of seeing the health and education sector receive the necessary equipment and as a catalyst to make Katoro a highly academic city,‚Äù Geita Regional Commissioner Ms Rosemary Senyamule thanked NMB Bank for providing support to Katoro Health Center and the Geita based schools. "Thank you very much NMB you have continued to be a great help to us the people of Katoro and Geita in general I am very grateful your bank has been very supportive to our Government" Ms Senyamule said. On her side the headmistress of Msufini Primary School, Ms Anita Mahalu, thanked NMB Bank for bringing desks to their school.